\f0\fs24 \cf0 PROJECT DESCRIPTION\
\
This project focuses on predicting whether an internet user will click on an online advertisement.\
\
The dataset contains information about user behavior and demographic characteristics such as age, internet usage, time spent on website, income level, and location.\
\
The goal of the project is to build a machine learning model that can predict whether a user will click on an advertisement.\
\
This problem is a Binary Classification problem because the output has only two possible classes:\
\
0 \uc0\u8594  User did not click the advertisement  \
1 \uc0\u8594  User clicked the advertisement\
\
Several machine learning algorithms can be used for this task including:\
\
- Logistic Regression\
- k-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)\
- Random Forest Classifier\
\
In this project, these algorithms are used to learn patterns in user behavior and predict the likelihood of clicking an advertisement.\
\
The performance of the model can be evaluated using classification metrics such as:\
\
- Accuracy\
- Precision\
- Recall\
- F1 Score\
- Confusion Matrix\
\
Possible applications of this project include:\
\
- Digital marketing optimization\
- Targeted advertising\
- Customer behavior analysis\
- Online marketing strategy}